OL,3,CMum 'went numb' as daughter's severe
OL,4,Casthma left her fighting for breath
OL,6,FDr Liz Gamble, a Consultant
OL,7,FRespiratory Physician at the Bristol
OL,8,FRoyal Infirmary, said: "Severe asthma
OL,9,Fis often identified too late so people
OL,10,Ftend to see their GP too late or come
OL,11,Fto the hospital too late and delay
OL,12,Fseeking help when they're struggling
OL,13,Fwith symptoms.
OL,15,F"One of the key things that we should
OL,16,Fbe doing is making sure people's
OL,17,Fasthma is well controlled day-to-day."
OL,19,FElisha's asthma is now well managed -
OL,20,Fbut it's taken years of consideration
OL,21,Fand work to get there.
